{"name": "oscilloscopy", "metadata": {"name": "oscilloscopy", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "License :: Other/Proprietary License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Magmoc/oscilloscopy", "license": "LICENSE", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pandas", "pydantic"], "summary": "A Python package to parse oscilloscope data.", "upload_time": 1734189424}, "documentation": ["# oscilloscopy\n\n`oscilloscopy` is a Python package to easily parse oscilloscope data. \n\n## Installation\n\nUse the package manager [pip](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/) to install oscilloscopy.\n\n```bash\npip install oscilloscopy\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nimport oscilloscopy\n\n# Returns the OscilloscopeData struct with all the data\ndata = oscilloscopy.from_csv(\"F0001CH1.CSV\")\n\n# Or\n\n# The folder probably contains a bitmap, a set, and one or two channel data csvs.\ndata = oscilloscopy.from_folder(\"./OSCILLOSCOPE_FOLDER/\")\n\n# Get timestamp data\ntime = data.channel_1.time\n\n# Get data points\nvalues = data.channel_1.data\n\n# Access the parameters\nunit = data.channel_1.parameters.vertical_units\n\n# Returns `None` or channel_2 data\ndata.channel_2\n\n# Plot the data\nplt.plot(time, values)\n```\n\n## Currently supported oscilloscopes\n\nIt can currently parse the data from the following oscilloscopes:\n\n- (semi-untested) TDS2000C Digital Storage Oscilloscope\n\n## Contributing\n\nPull requests are welcome. For major changes, please open an issue first\nto discuss what you would like to change.\n\nPlease make sure to update tests as appropriate.\n\n\n## License\n\n[MIT](https://choosealicense.com/licenses/mit/)\n\n## Roadmap\n- [ ] Verify working of library\n- [ ] Math Functionality?\n- [ ] Plotting Functionality?\n- [ ] Live connection with the USB?\n- [ ] Add more oscilloscopes\n\n## Authors\nCreated for use in the labs for the Electrical Engineering Bachelor of TU Delft\n\n- Erik van Weelderen, December 2024\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "oscilloscopy", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "oscilloscopy.Channel", "xref": {"fqname": "oscilloscopy.classes.Channel", "project": null}}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.OscilloscopeData", "xref": {"fqname": "oscilloscopy.oscilloscopedata.OscilloscopeData", "project": null}}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.Parameters", "xref": {"fqname": "oscilloscopy.classes.Parameters", "project": null}}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.ParameterType", "xref": {"fqname": "oscilloscopy.classes.ParameterType", "project": null}}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.Unit", "xref": {"fqname": "oscilloscopy.classes.Unit", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.errors", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "oscilloscopy.errors.OscilloscoPyError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.errors.NoChannelDataPresentError", "bases": ["OscilloscoPyError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.errors.CustomFolderStructureError", "bases": ["OscilloscoPyError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.errors.EmptyFolderError", "bases": ["OscilloscoPyError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.errors.InvalidParameterError", "bases": ["OscilloscoPyError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "oscilloscopy.errors.MissingParameterError", "bases": ["OscilloscoPyError"], "methods": [], "class_v